{"updated_at": "2012-02-01T13:40:43Z", "repo": "rails", "created_at": "2012-02-01T13:38:29Z", "owner": "rails", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/3758836", "id": 3758836, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/3946", "issue_id": 3946, "user": {"repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/pokonski/repos", "type": "User", "html_url": "https://github.com/pokonski", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/pokonski/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/pokonski/subscriptions", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/pokonski/following{/other_user}", "gravatar_id": "b6be565dc21f521acf0193ee63ab9d0a", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/pokonski/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/pokonski", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/pokonski/gists{/gist_id}", "avatar_url": "https://2.gravatar.com/avatar/b6be565dc21f521acf0193ee63ab9d0a?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2Fc859637e6138a4656c26afe2867914c6.png", "id": 135402, "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/pokonski/events{/privacy}", "login": "pokonski", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/pokonski/received_events", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/pokonski/followers"}, "body": "Once precompiled they land in public/assets. I don't know how you configured your nginx so can't help you precisely. But you should not touch config.assets.prefix at all.\r\n\r\nhttp://guides.rubyonrails.org/configuring.html says:\r\n\r\n`config.action_controller.relative_url_root` can be used to tell Rails that you are deploying to a subdirectory. The default is `ENV['RAILS_RELATIVE_URL_ROOT']`\r\n\r\nTry and set that in environments/development.rb. Also notice the **action_controller** part, it's important.", "_id": {"$oid": "52382f63bd3543c15100f52a"}, "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/3946#issuecomment-3758836"}
